    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nIt's currently possible to anchor floating windows relative to the editor, to a window, to the cursor or to the mouse. It'd be useful to also allow anchoring relative to a buffer's extmark.\r\n\r\nFor example, this could be used when displaying:\r\n\r\n- on-hover infos w/ `vim.lsp.buf.hover`;\r\n- the signature of the function the user's typing (e.g. [lsp_signature.nvim](https://github.com/ray-x/lsp_signature.nvim));\r\n- in-depth git blame infos on a particular line.\r\n\r\nAt the moment this is done by using floats that appear to be anchored at the correct position when they're created, but that immediately go out-of-sync if the buffer is scrolled or if the terminal window is resized.\r\n\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/59321248/f1b7ff3e-0e18-44d2-9893-7b143bf82d20\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\n`nvim_open_win`'s opts accept a new `extmark: extmark_id` pair, and the `relative` opt can be set to `\"extmark\"`. The resulting floating window moves when the extmark moves, and is cutoff/hidden if the extmark is in a region of the buffer that's outside the viewport.\r\n\r\nQ: should there be an option to specify whether the same float is displayed on every window split that's housing the buffer the extmark is on?",
